End to End tests with a docker client

Why:
Allows us to run headless (although it is really chrome) tests

How:
We are using the following image https://hub.docker.com/r/webnicer/protractor-headless/

Architecture:
- server (our flask app)
- client (docker container running protractor and chrome)

Usage:
  build and run the server
  $ make
  $ make run

  run the docker image
  $ cd test/e2e-tests
  $ docker run -it --rm --privileged --net=host -v /dev/shm:/dev/shm -v $(pwd):/tests shusson/chrome-tester protractor



WARNING:
If you are using `docker for mac` you will have to manually tell the container how to connect to the host
see (https://forums.docker.com/t/access-host-not-vm-from-inside-container/11747/10)

    For example:
    $ sudo ifconfig lo0 alias 10.200.10.1/24
    $ docker run -it --rm --privileged --net=host --add-host=docker.local:10.200.10.1 -v /dev/shm:/dev/shm \
      -v $(pwd):/tests shusson/chrome-tester protractor --baseUrl='http://docker.local:5013'